  29. ‌let force f x =
  30.   match !x with
  31.   | Done x -> x
  32.   | Raise e -> raise e
  33.   | Thunk e ->
  34.       match f e with
  35.       | y ->
  36.         x := Done y;
  37.         y
  38.       | exception e ->
  39.         x := Raise e;
  40.         raise e

  42. ‌let get_arg x =

  45. ‌let get_contents x =

  47.   | Thunk a -> Either.Left a
  48.   | Done b -> Either.Right b
  49.   | Raise e -> raise e

  63. ‌let force_logged log f x =
  64.   match !x with
  65.   | Done x -> x
  66.   | Raise e -> raise e
  67.   | Thunk e ->
  68.     match f e with
  69.     | (Error _ as err : _ result) ->
  70.         x := Done err;
  71.         log := Cons(x, e, !log);
  72.         err
  73.     | Ok _ as res ->
  74.         x := Done res;
  75.         res
  76.     | exception e ->
  77.         x := Raise e;
  78.         raise e

  80. ‌let backtrack log =
  81.   let rec loop = function
  82.     | Nil -> ()
  83.     | Cons(x, e, rest) ->
  84.         x := Thunk e;
  85.         loop rest
  86.   in
  87.   loop !log
